# Pre-push lint guard.
#
# `bun run lint` is fast (~6s) and catches the kind of regression that
# previously sat red on `main` for 14+ releases (an unused-assignment
# warning that nobody noticed because the npm publish workflow isn't
# gated on Quality checks). Pre-push (not pre-commit) is the right
# granularity: it stays out of the way of normal commits but blocks
# the git operation that would actually expose the failure to CI.
bun run lint
